review_blob: Poor mans Dark Lord.  Tasty, split one with a friend.  Head quickly dissipates, leaving sweet, smoky ale.
Simply a great Trappist beer.  Slightly raisin scent and taste but with many other complexities.
A lees potent version of the Quad (still 9.3%).  Lighter in color, not quite a sweet, but still not hoppy.  Great Tripel.
Sweet, not at all hoppy, strong but not overwhelming, great aroma, warm fire and a bottle o Quad, good to go.
